    Port new shadcn UI onto Next.js frontend, wired to wallet + Go API
    
    Implement the polished newFront UI inside the existing Next.js 14 app
    (frontend/, bun) while keeping the previous frontend's real functionality,
    connections, and dependencies.
    
    - Tailwind v4 tokens -> v3 (RGB-channel CSS vars + tailwind.config), Outfit/
      JetBrains Mono via next/font.
    - react-router -> Next app-router: 9 routes in src/app/*/page.tsx rendering
      client views in src/views/.
    - Ported the shadcn subset actually used (button, input, progress, badge, tabs,
      sonner) + educhain shared/layout; added React 18-compatible deps via bun.
    - Real wiring: onboarding (verifyMatric -> DID -> wallet connect -> signMessage
      -> bindWallet), marketplace (listCourses), verification (verifyCert added to
      api.ts), sidebar wallet chip + disconnect via useWallet.
    - next.config: inert DISABLE_WEBPACK_CACHE escape hatch for low-disk builds.
    
    Verified: tsc --noEmit clean and full next build succeeds (all routes prerender).
    
